org.sbml.squeezer
Enum CfgKeys

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<CfgKeys>
      org.sbml.squeezer.CfgKeys
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<CfgKeys>
public enum CfgKeys
extends Enum<CfgKeys>

This is a list of possible command line options and configuration of SBMLsqueezer. Each element listed here determins a key for a configuration value.

Since:
1.3
Author:
Andreas Dräger andreas.draeger@uni-tuebingen.de

TYPE_UNIT_CONSISTENCY

public static final CfgKeys TYPE_UNIT_CONSISTENCY
How to ensure unit consistency in kinetic equations? One way is to set each participating species to an initial amount and to set the unit to mmole. The other way is to set the initial concentration of each species, set the unit to mmole per l and to multiply the species with the size of the surrounding compartment whenever it occurs in a kinetic equation. Hence, this type paramter belongs to two values.

OPT_ALL_REACTIONS_ARE_ENZYME_CATALYZED

public static final CfgKeys OPT_ALL_REACTIONS_ARE_ENZYME_CATALYZED
If true, all reactions within the network are considered enzyme reactions. If false, an explicit enzymatic catalyst must be assigned to a reaction to obtain this status.

OPT_IGNORE_THESE_SPECIES_WHEN_CREATING_LAWS

public static final CfgKeys OPT_IGNORE_THESE_SPECIES_WHEN_CREATING_LAWS
Allows the user to ignore species that are annotated with the given compound identifiers when creating rate laws for reactions that involve these species. For instance, water or single protons can often be ignored when creating rate equations, hence simplifying the resulting rate equations. Preselected are the KEGG compound identifiers for water and protons
